252
00:11:11.963 --> 00:11:14.108
Why not give them a chance?

253
00:11:14.132 --> 00:11:15.651
Perhaps there is more
than meets the eye

254
00:11:15.675 --> 00:11:16.861
with these warriors.

255
00:11:16.885 --> 00:11:20.055
- [SNORING]
- Eh?

256
00:11:21.098 --> 00:11:23.034
Yeah. doubt it.

257
00:11:23.058 --> 00:11:25.036
Let's just call in
Agar's Assassins again.

258
00:11:25.060 --> 00:11:29.123
Uh. Agar apparently had his hand
chopped off in a barroom brawl.

259
00:11:29.147 --> 00:11:30.875
[QUIETLY] Oh. shit.

260
00:11:30.899 --> 00:11:33.068
- [HIGH-PITCHED RINGING]
- [GRUNTS]

261
00:11:35.237 --> 00:11:36.923
[URIEL] Very well.

262
00:11:36.947 --> 00:11:38.716
You're hired. Vox Machina.

263
00:11:38.740 --> 00:11:40.885
Mainly because I like the bear.

264
00:11:40.909 --> 00:11:43.596
Lady Allura will accompany you
to the Shale Steps.

265
00:11:43.620 --> 00:11:45.914
the village closest
to the last attack.

266
00:11:47.457 --> 00:11:50.019
So. what exactly are we killing.

267
00:11:50.043 --> 00:11:52.230
and how much are we making?

268
00:11:52.254 --> 00:11:54.148
[KRIEG] We don't know
what you're killing.

269
00:11:54.172 --> 00:11:56.466
but once you kill it.
all this is yours.

270
00:11:58.593 --> 00:12:00.696
[SCANLAN] Uh. one more question.

271
00:12:00.720 --> 00:12:02.240
Yeah. how are we supposed
to get there?

272
00:12:07.853 --> 00:12:09.688
[GIGGLES]

273
00:12:14.276 --> 00:12:16.879
[VEX] Brother.
I am telling you I felt it.

274
00:12:16.903 --> 00:12:18.506
right there in the throne room.

275
00:12:18.530 --> 00:12:20.258
I haven't felt that since...

276
00:12:20.282 --> 00:12:21.676
Isn't this ship amazing?

277
00:12:21.700 --> 00:12:23.719
There's two bathrooms
downstairs.

278
00:12:23.743 --> 00:12:26.013
Hey. by the way.
why are you both whispering

279
00:12:26.037 --> 00:12:28.766
- like we can't hear you?
- Can you mind your business for once. gnome?

280
00:12:28.790 --> 00:12:30.726
[MUTTERING]

281
00:12:30.750 --> 00:12:33.187
As you can see.
the creature has already razed

282
00:12:33.211 --> 00:12:36.566
three villages
and miles of farmland.

283
00:12:36.590 --> 00:12:38.776
If this evil persists.

284
00:12:38.800 --> 00:12:41.779
the kingdom
will starve to death.

285
00:12:41.803 --> 00:12:45.116
This mission sounds
kind of deadly. [CHUCKLES]

286
00:12:45.140 --> 00:12:47.326
- Do we really want to do this?
- Yes. this task

287
00:12:47.350 --> 00:12:51.122
is dangerous. which is why
only the most noble. heroic

288
00:12:51.146 --> 00:12:53.416
- and true...
- Yeah. yeah. nobility and heroism

289
00:12:53.440 --> 00:12:56.127
is fine and all. but we're
in this for the money.

290
00:12:56.151 --> 00:12:59.797
I see. So it's coin
over character.

291
00:12:59.821 --> 00:13:02.008
Not surprising.

292
00:13:02.032 --> 00:13:04.034
- [WIND WHISTLING]
- [WOOD CREAKING]

293
00:13:11.541 --> 00:13:12.935
[GRUNTS]

294
00:13:12.959 --> 00:13:15.521
The Shale Steps are beyond
that hill. Good luck.

295
00:13:15.545 --> 00:13:20.193
Please don't. oh.
fuck this up. as they say.

296
00:13:20.217 --> 00:13:21.694
Thanks for the sweet ride.

297
00:13:21.718 --> 00:13:23.720
You'll be back to pick us
up later. right?

298
00:13:26.890 --> 00:13:28.409
[BIRDS CAWING]

299
00:13:28.433 --> 00:13:30.602
Yeah. she'll be back.

300
00:13:38.568 --> 00:13:40.129
What we doing here again?

301
00:13:40.153 --> 00:13:42.089
The last attack
was just south of here.

302
00:13:42.113 --> 00:13:44.300
We're gonna ask around.
see if anyone knows anything.

303
00:13:44.324 --> 00:13:45.927
Ask around.

304
00:13:45.951 --> 00:13:47.970
[KEYLETH] Excuse me.
green friends.

305
00:13:47.994 --> 00:13:51.140
Have you seen any evil wizards
or giant monsters

306
00:13:51.164 --> 00:13:52.517
passing through here?

307
00:13:52.541 --> 00:13:54.501
- Uh...
- That's kind of weird.

308
00:13:55.794 --> 00:13:58.022
[FISHERMAN] Nah.
it was too foggy.

309
00:13:58.046 --> 00:14:00.816
All we saw was dark clouds.
lightning.

310
00:14:00.840 --> 00:14:02.443
We thought it was a storm.

311
00:14:02.467 --> 00:14:04.820
Oh. you didn't see
anything. huh?

312
00:14:04.844 --> 00:14:09.242
How convenient. Mr. Fisherman.
if that is your real name.

313
00:14:09.266 --> 00:14:12.745
- Whoa...
- Okay. maybe let me handle the questioning. Scanlan.

314
00:14:12.769 --> 00:14:15.414
I'm sorry about him.

315
00:14:15.438 --> 00:14:17.250
[MOTHER] You're a priest
of sorts. aren't you?

316
00:14:17.274 --> 00:14:19.293
Could you bless our house?

317
00:14:19.317 --> 00:14:20.753
- Protect it from this evil?
- Uh...

318
00:14:20.777 --> 00:14:22.797
A-A blessing?
Yeah. yeah. yeah. sure.

319
00:14:22.821 --> 00:14:24.590
Uh. no problem.

320
00:14:24.614 --> 00:14:26.801
Okay. here goes.

321
00:14:26.825 --> 00:14:32.348
May the Everlight
shine upon your home.

322
00:14:32.372 --> 00:14:34.433
Everything will be tip-top.

323
00:14:34.457 --> 00:14:36.561
Okay. I'm sure you'll survive
these trying times.

324
00:14:36.585 --> 00:14:39.713
so. good luck?

325
00:14:40.839 --> 00:14:43.526
Are you sure
you're a holy person?

326
00:14:43.550 --> 00:14:45.778
Yeah. I'm-I'm just.
uh. out of practice.

327
00:14:45.802 --> 00:14:48.114
I don't really bless
a lot of houses these days.

328
00:14:48.138 --> 00:14:49.991
Thank you. dear.

329
00:14:50.015 --> 00:14:52.827
I'm sure it'll be enough
to keep our family safe.

330
00:14:52.851 --> 00:14:54.060
[GASPS]

331
00:14:55.061 --> 00:14:57.105
Wow.

332
00:14:58.607 --> 00:15:00.501
- Are you a wizard?
- [CHUCKLES]

333
00:15:00.525 --> 00:15:03.254
Nah. The magic's all
in the fingers. kid.

334
00:15:03.278 --> 00:15:05.172
[GASPS]

335
00:15:05.196 --> 00:15:06.966
Wow.

336
00:15:06.990 --> 00:15:09.885
And now it's in yours.

337
00:15:09.909 --> 00:15:11.387
Whoa.

338
00:15:11.411 --> 00:15:13.598
That's real silver.
Keep it safe.

339
00:15:13.622 --> 00:15:15.474
There's a monster roaming about.

340
00:15:15.498 --> 00:15:16.851
- You mean flying.
- What's that?

341
00:15:16.875 --> 00:15:18.769
Something flew right over us.

342
00:15:18.793 --> 00:15:20.271
It knocked down
the big tree on the hill.

343
00:15:20.295 --> 00:15:24.400
We heard wings beating but
we couldn't see it in the storm.

344
00:15:24.424 --> 00:15:26.694
But it was big. Really big.

345
00:15:26.718 --> 00:15:27.927
Yeah.

346
00:15:33.183 --> 00:15:34.452
[BIRDS SQUAWKING]

347
00:15:34.476 --> 00:15:36.203
[VEX] Get over here.

348
00:15:36.227 --> 00:15:38.480
- Trinket found something.
- [SNIFFING]

349
00:15:40.065 --> 00:15:42.168
The tracks are too muddy
to discern.

350
00:15:42.192 --> 00:15:44.211
But it looks like
it took to the air

351
00:15:44.235 --> 00:15:45.820
and flew along the coast.

352
00:15:48.657 --> 00:15:50.992
- Whoa. [CHUCKLES]
- [GRUNTS]

353
00:15:52.035 --> 00:15:53.429
Think you'll be needing this.

354
00:15:53.453 --> 00:15:55.080
Ah.

355
00:16:04.589 --> 00:16:06.317
Now they look...

356
00:16:06.341 --> 00:16:07.842
human?

357
00:16:11.971 --> 00:16:14.116
[GRUNTS] It's close.

358
00:16:14.140 --> 00:16:15.767
Everyone. get ready.

359
00:16:18.520 --> 00:16:20.480
[RUSTLING]

360
00:16:26.111 --> 00:16:28.673
[BLEATS]

361
00:16:28.697 --> 00:16:31.592
[LAUGHS] Get the fuck out.

362
00:16:31.616 --> 00:16:34.595
What. a little lamb
was behind all the mayhem?

363
00:16:34.619 --> 00:16:36.430
Oh. don't let that thing
bite you. Vex.

364
00:16:36.454 --> 00:16:38.456
[GRUNTING]

365
00:16:40.875 --> 00:16:42.770
[BLEATING]

366
00:16:42.794 --> 00:16:44.462
[BEAST SNARLING]

367
00:16:50.051 --> 00:16:51.428
Oh. fuck. oh. fuck. oh. fuck.

368
00:16:53.179 --> 00:16:54.389
Fuck!

369
00:17:05.817 --> 00:17:07.670
[SHOUTS]

370
00:17:07.694 --> 00:17:09.863
- [PANTING]
- [ROARS]

371
00:17:21.166 --> 00:17:24.002
[GRUNTS. PANTING]

372
00:17:26.337 --> 00:17:27.815
[BOOMING STEP]

373
00:17:27.839 --> 00:17:30.592
- I suggest we run. Right now!
- [GROG] Fuck that.

374
00:17:31.593 --> 00:17:32.820
We fight!

375
00:17:32.844 --> 00:17:34.071
[ROARING]

376
00:17:34.095 --> 00:17:36.014
Grog. you dumb. brave asshole!

377
00:17:37.307 --> 00:17:38.576
[GROG ROARING]

378
00:17:38.600 --> 00:17:41.144
[GRUNTING]

379
00:17:43.646 --> 00:17:46.858
[GASPS] Grog's down already?
Come on!

380
00:17:49.778 --> 00:17:51.154
[GROWLS]

381
00:17:52.363 --> 00:17:53.448
[GRUNTING]

382
00:17:56.534 --> 00:17:57.702
[LOW GROWL]

383
00:18:00.246 --> 00:18:01.682
[SCREECHES]

384
00:18:01.706 --> 00:18:04.685
Keyleth!
A little magic might help.

385
00:18:04.709 --> 00:18:06.252
[GASPING BREATHS]

386
00:18:07.837 --> 00:18:10.173
- We're in serious trouble here.
- [DRAGON ROARS]

387
00:18:11.257 --> 00:18:13.778
Keyleth. snap out of it.
Keyleth!

388
00:18:13.802 --> 00:18:15.780
- Keyleth!
- Sorry. Um...

389
00:18:15.804 --> 00:18:17.096
Okay. Okay.

390
00:18:19.390 --> 00:18:21.601
[WHOOSHING]

391
00:18:22.644 --> 00:18:24.455
[THUNDER CRASHING]

392
00:18:24.479 --> 00:18:27.524
[SNARLS]

393
00:18:29.192 --> 00:18:31.504
[FIERCE YELL]

394
00:18:31.528 --> 00:18:33.655
[THUNDER CRASHING. WIND RUSHING]

395
00:18:39.035 --> 00:18:41.639
Did I just make it worse?

396
00:18:41.663 --> 00:18:42.914
[ROARS]

397
00:18:44.082 --> 00:18:45.935
[SHIELD WHIRRING]

398
00:18:45.959 --> 00:18:47.252
[GROWLING]

399
00:18:48.670 --> 00:18:50.564
[LOUD RUMBLING]

400
00:18:50.588 --> 00:18:52.316
- [VEX] Look out!
- [GASPING]

401
00:18:52.340 --> 00:18:54.217
[DEBRIS SETTLING]

402
00:18:56.261 --> 00:18:58.364
[BOOMING STEPS]

403
00:18:58.388 --> 00:19:00.741
[SNIFFING. GRUNTING]

404
00:19:00.765 --> 00:19:02.475
[LOW GROWL]

405
00:19:04.519 --> 00:19:06.104
[DRAGON SCREECHES]

406
00:19:07.814 --> 00:19:11.043
[WINGBEATS RECEDE IN DISTANCE]

407
00:19:11.067 --> 00:19:13.254
[SCANLAN] Uh. get me out.
Get-get me out!

408
00:19:13.278 --> 00:19:15.923
I'm trapped under Grog's ass!

409
00:19:15.947 --> 00:19:17.716
[STRAINING]

410
00:19:17.740 --> 00:19:19.009
[PERCY] So...

411
00:19:19.033 --> 00:19:22.453
this is what rock bottom
feels like.

412
00:19:24.372 --> 00:19:26.183
At least we're still alive.

413
00:19:26.207 --> 00:19:27.810
thank the Everlight.

414
00:19:27.834 --> 00:19:30.771
And thanks to Keyleth
for the giant shrub.

415
00:19:30.795 --> 00:19:33.983
But did you have to make it
so thorny? [GROANS]

416
00:19:34.007 --> 00:19:37.027
That dragon. We almost... died.

417
00:19:37.051 --> 00:19:38.195
[PANTS]

418
00:19:38.219 --> 00:19:40.698
Except we didn't die.
Because of you. Keyleth.

419
00:19:40.722 --> 00:19:42.157
You hear me?

420
00:19:42.181 --> 00:19:44.601
We're alive because of you.

421
00:19:46.644 --> 00:19:48.831
- Grog. You're hurt.
- Nah.

422
00:19:48.855 --> 00:19:50.916
Just a flesh wound. No big.

423
00:19:50.940 --> 00:19:53.711
[GROANS]
Question: Is this normal?

424
00:19:53.735 --> 00:19:55.796
- Oh. no. - Holy shit.
- I'm gonna throw up.

425
00:19:55.820 --> 00:19:57.339
Hold still. old friend.

426
00:19:57.363 --> 00:19:58.591
I got you.

427
00:19:58.615 --> 00:19:59.908
[WHIRRING]

428
00:20:03.119 --> 00:20:04.263
[GROANING]

429
00:20:04.287 --> 00:20:06.390
Oh. I feel better already.

430
00:20:06.414 --> 00:20:08.851
Thanks. Pike. You're the best.

431
00:20:08.875 --> 00:20:11.437
[SIGHS]
That... took a lot out of me.

432
00:20:11.461 --> 00:20:12.855
- I got you.
- Oh.

433
00:20:12.879 --> 00:20:15.441
Uh. thanks.

434
00:20:15.465 --> 00:20:17.318
Oh. uh. you can put me down now.

435
00:20:17.342 --> 00:20:18.903
Oh. Yeah.

436
00:20:18.927 --> 00:20:20.529
Uh... yeah.

437
00:20:20.553 --> 00:20:23.449
All right.
fuck Uriel and all of this.

438
00:20:23.473 --> 00:20:25.117
we're done here.

439
00:20:25.141 --> 00:20:27.244
We didn't sign up
for certain death.

440
00:20:27.268 --> 00:20:30.039
Must I remind you
we gave our word to the council?

441
00:20:30.063 --> 00:20:32.416
That should probably
mean something.

442
00:20:32.440 --> 00:20:34.835
Oh. who gives a soggy anus
about the council?

443
00:20:34.859 --> 00:20:38.297
The only word I care about
is "Scanlan Shorthalt."

444
00:20:38.321 --> 00:20:40.257
And yes.
I know that's two words.

445
00:20:40.281 --> 00:20:42.259
but you know what I'm saying.

446
00:20:42.283 --> 00:20:45.179
Yeah. What have those
fuckity-fucks ever done for us?

447
00:20:45.203 --> 00:20:47.431
Except give us a job
and a bunch of gold

448
00:20:47.455 --> 00:20:49.433
and treasure and stuff?

449
00:20:49.457 --> 00:20:51.644
We've fought a lot of things...

450
00:20:51.668 --> 00:20:52.978
but a dragon?

451
00:20:53.002 --> 00:20:54.730
An actual dragon?

452
00:20:54.754 --> 00:20:56.941
It's not about the council.

453
00:20:56.965 --> 00:20:59.151
or the contract...
it's about these people.

454
00:20:59.175 --> 00:21:00.527
They need us.

455
00:21:00.551 --> 00:21:02.780
We can't just run away.

456
00:21:02.804 --> 00:21:05.199
This is why I hate traveling
with holy people.

457
00:21:05.223 --> 00:21:07.576
- They're too goddamned good.
- [VEX] Pike...

458
00:21:07.600 --> 00:21:09.954
this creature is beyond us.

459
00:21:09.978 --> 00:21:12.456
When Vex and I were young.

460
00:21:12.480 --> 00:21:14.583
one of those monsters
killed our mother.

461
00:21:14.607 --> 00:21:17.211
I've studied dragons
my entire life. hoping to find

462
00:21:17.235 --> 00:21:18.379
the one that did it.

463
00:21:18.403 --> 00:21:19.546
I can...

464
00:21:19.570 --> 00:21:21.423
feel when they're close.

465
00:21:21.447 --> 00:21:24.218
A horrid pain in my head.

466
00:21:24.242 --> 00:21:25.719
Then it's settled.

467
00:21:25.743 --> 00:21:27.972
We'll go back to the palace
and get out of the contract.

468
00:21:27.996 --> 00:21:29.765
You don't understand. Percy.

469
00:21:29.789 --> 00:21:32.101
I felt it there. too.
at the palace.

470
00:21:32.125 --> 00:21:34.103
Y-You're just
telling us this now?

471
00:21:34.127 --> 00:21:35.854
I'm sorry. I...

472
00:21:35.878 --> 00:21:38.190
I wasn't certain
until the dragon...

473
00:21:38.214 --> 00:21:40.567
It's been years since Mother...

474
00:21:40.591 --> 00:21:42.194
Are you sure. Vex'ahlia?

475
00:21:42.218 --> 00:21:44.363
I know what I felt.
Someone on the council

476
00:21:44.387 --> 00:21:47.074
must have been in contact
with the dragon. or...

477
00:21:47.098 --> 00:21:50.911
I don't know.
but I-I'm sure it was real.

478
00:21:50.935 --> 00:21:53.372
Then we walk away
from all of this.

479
00:21:53.396 --> 00:21:55.791
It's not worth it.
You heard her.

480
00:21:55.815 --> 00:21:58.544
One of them might be working
with that monster.

481
00:21:58.568 --> 00:22:00.629
Let's just get
the hell out of here

482
00:22:00.653 --> 00:22:03.882
and never set foot
in Emon again.

483
00:22:03.906 --> 00:22:06.385
Can we all agree on that?

484
00:22:06.409 --> 00:22:08.411
♪ ♪

485
00:22:25.887 --> 00:22:28.056
♪ ♪

486
00:22:49.243 --> 00:22:51.496
Oh. no.

487
00:22:53.456 --> 00:22:57.668
[VEX] They wiped them out.
all of them.

488
00:23:01.464 --> 00:23:04.050
[STIFLES SOB]

489
00:23:12.767 --> 00:23:15.228
♪ ♪

490
00:23:32.411 --> 00:23:34.914
[WEAK GROANING NEARBY]

491
00:23:36.916 --> 00:23:38.334
[WEAK GROAN]

492
00:23:39.127 --> 00:23:41.355
- [STRAINING]
- [WOOD CREAKING]

493
00:23:41.379 --> 00:23:44.191
[GRUNTING]

494
00:23:44.215 --> 00:23:46.425
[VAX] Pike! Get over here!

495
00:23:48.344 --> 00:23:50.322
[GROANING WEAKLY]

496
00:23:50.346 --> 00:23:52.074
[PIKE] Please. Everlight.

497
00:23:52.098 --> 00:23:54.076
let your power reach him.

498
00:23:54.100 --> 00:23:55.744
Pike. Please.

499
00:23:55.768 --> 00:23:57.371
Shit!

500
00:23:57.395 --> 00:23:59.748
No. I can't do it.

501
00:23:59.772 --> 00:24:02.400
I'm still too weak from before.

502
00:24:04.443 --> 00:24:06.255
[GRUNTS WEAKLY. EXHALES]

503
00:24:06.279 --> 00:24:08.865
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

504
00:24:13.161 --> 00:24:14.745
We could have stopped this.

505
00:24:15.788 --> 00:24:17.415
Should have.

506
00:24:19.584 --> 00:24:21.770
[SCANLAN PLUCKING.
TUNING STRINGED INSTRUMENT]

507
00:24:21.794 --> 00:24:24.773
♪ ♪

508
00:24:24.797 --> 00:24:26.525
What the hell
are you doing. Scanlan?

509
00:24:26.549 --> 00:24:29.736
Thinking of a rhyme
for "dead dragon."

510
